   Privacy Statement
   FirstGov for Seniors is an official web site of the United States
   government. We understand that privacy is an important issue for
   visitors to our site. Our privacy policy below addresses your concerns
   about what information is collected, how its collected and how it is
   used.

   Who Is FirstGov for Seniors?

   This web site is provided as a public service by the the Social
   Security Administration with additional funding from the Chief
   Information Officers Council, and affiliation with FirstGov.gov, and a
   number of federal agencies who deal with senior issues.

   Information Collection and Use

   We will not obtain personally identifying information about you when
   you visit our site unless you choose to provide us with such
   information.

   We provide a feature (Ask Us/Tell Us) that allows you to fill out a
   form with your personal information and submit it to us through our web
   site or by email. If you choose to provide us with personal information
   in this manner, we use that information solely to respond to your
   message and get you the information you have requested.

                Our concern about sending personal information
                                  via email
      Electronic mail is not secure. Therefore, we suggest that you dont
      send personal information via email. We will only send you general
                            information via email.


   [blubul3a.gif] We share the information you give us with another
   government agency only if your inquiry relates to that agency, or as
   otherwise required by law.
   [blubul3a.gif] We do not create individual profiles with the
   information you provide nor do we give it to any private organizations
   or use it for commercial marketing.
   [blubul3a.gif] Electronic mail messages that meet the definition of
   records in the Federal Records Act (44 U.S.C. 3101 et seq.) are covered
   under the same disposition schedule as all other Federal records. This
   means that emails you send will be preserved and maintained for varying
   periods of time if those emails meet the definition of Federal records.
   Electronic messages that are not records are deleted when no longer
   needed.

   We have a Newsletter Subscription Service that requires submission of
   an email address. It is used only for the purpose of sending the weekly
   newsletter.
   [blubul3a.gif] We do not share this information with any other agency
   or entity.
   [blubul3a.gif] We do not create individual profiles with the
   information you provide nor do we give it to any private organizations
   or use it for commercial marketing.

   For site management purposes, we collect a variety of information
   including: browser type, originating domain address (e.g., aol.com),
   page locations visited, and other miscellaneous site references.
   [blubul3a.gif] Our system uses software programs to create summary
   statistics, which are used for web site planning and maintenance,
   determining technical design specifications, and analyzing system
   performance.
   [blubul3a.gif] For security purposes, and to ensure that this service
   remains available to all users, our computer system employs software
   programs to monitor network traffic, to identify unauthorized attempts
   to upload or change information, to cause damage, or to deny service to
   authorized users.
   [blubul3a.gif] Except for authorized law enforcement investigations and
   as stated above, no other attempts are made to identify individual
   users or their usage habits. We do not collect cookies. Server logs as
   described above are scheduled for regular destruction in accordance
   with National Archives and Records Administration General Schedule 20.

   When you use a link on the FirstGov for Seniors site to go to another
   web site, our privacy policy no longer applies. If you wish to know the
   privacy policy of the site where you are going, contact the webmaster
   of that site.

   Use of the FirstGov for Seniors Site

   Information presented on the site is considered public information and
   may be distributed or copied for non-commercial purposes. Use of
   appropriate byline/photo/image credits is requested.

   Unauthorized attempts to upload information or change information on
   this web-site are strictly prohibited and may be punishable under the
   Computer Fraud and Abuse Act of 1986, the National Information
   Infrastructure Protection Act and other applicable laws. Violation of
   these laws could include criminal penalties.




